So U came in here this evening expecting to walk into a normal grocery store, and I was surprised to see that it's not a grocery store at all.  Not even close.  I would characterize this place as a very limited convenience store, with a sandwich and coffee section included.  The sandwich options seemed pretty decent, so I ended up ordering a roasted chicken sandwich that included mostly vegetables.  The vegetables included cucumbers, tomatoes, onions, and ranch dressing.  On top of that,I purchased a prepared chef salad.  I waited around inside of the store which the person behind the counter was preparing this.  I asked another employee if I could use the restroom, and she gleefully indicated to me that the restrooms were closed due to the pandemic. I was fine with it, but as I walked away I could here this employee high fiving another employee and laughing about the fact that she refused to let me use the restroom. I don't know that their amusement was the actual result of what was told to me.  But I felt offended either way,not because the restroom was closed, but because I felt that these employees were making a joke about it.  I left with the chicken sandwich and salad, and I hope it turns out to be something decent by the time I can enjoy it at home.

This is by far the worst Wawa and even convenience store I have ever been!  The lack of professionalism and customer service is the worst I’ve ever seen.  You probably have over 12 staff on rotation and none are showing any sort of empathy to the customers trying to get something.  After I paid for a simple sandwich, had to wait over 30 minutes just to have a supervisor get someone to start preparing orders, and that was after I and several other complained.  On top of that, they didn’t even had Mac n Cheese, which btw I paid for like 40 minutes before.  It’s my fault to pick this store because I should have read the reviews and seen the atmosphere prior, but it was the only place open after 10 pm in Columbia Heights.  Please if you’re reading this, don’t support this store so hopefully Wawa can do something about this.
